properties.headline: Wind Chill Warning issued February 5 at 3:14AM MST until February 5 at 8:00AM MST by NWS Cheyenne WY
properties.description:
...DANGEROUS WIND CHILLS EARLY THIS MORNING FOR AREAS WEST OF THE
LARAMIE RANGE...

...BLOWING AND DRIFTING SNOW LIKELY IN THE WIND PRONE AREAS OF
SOUTHEAST WYOMING THROUGH MID DAY THURSDAY...

...BLIZZARD CONDITIONS POSSIBLE ALONG INTERSTATE 80 WEST OF
LARAMIE THURSDAY NIGHT AND FRIDAY...WITH HEAVY SNOW LIKELY
SPREADING INTO THE INTERSTATE 25 CORRIDOR...

* WHAT...Dangerously cold wind chills expected. Wind chills as low
as 40 below zero.

* WHERE...Interior valleys of Carbon and Albany Counties in
Wyoming.

* WHEN...Until 8 AM MST this morning.

* IMPACTS...The dangerously cold wind chills could cause
frostbite on exposed skin in as little as 10 minutes. Move
animals to shelter and avoid excessive outdoor exposure until
temperatures warm.
properties.instruction:
Avoid outside activities if possible. When outside, make sure you
wear appropriate clothing, a hat, and mittens.

NWSheadline: WIND CHILL WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 8 AM MST THIS MORNING
